{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q48764287]] Wikidata name: kami ashagi [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 07:18, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q48764287]] Wikidata name: kami ashagi [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 03:57, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} '''Kamiashagi''' (神アシャギ, 神アサギ) is a type of [[:en:Hut|hut]] used to conduct community deity festivals in the northern region of [[:en:Okinawa Island|Okinawa Main Island]]. These structures are characterized by an open interior with no [[:en:Wall|wall]], supported by either four or six pillars, lacking a floor structure, with extremely low eaves that require one to stoop in order to enter. The traditional style features a thatched [[:en:Roof|roof]] in the form of a [[:en:Hip roof|hip roof]], though in the postwar period, concrete constructions ([[:en:Concrete|concrete]]) have also appeared.<ref name=shimpo>[https://ryukyushimpo.jp/okinawa-dic/prentry-40953.html 最新版沖縄コンパクト事典]</ref>
[[File:Kami-Asagi.jpg|thumb|Kamiashagi|250px]]
== Overview == Kamiashagi is considered an ancient form of the shrine hall (tun) used as a venue for ritual ceremonies in central-southern [[:en:Okinawa Island|Okinawa Main Island]].<ref name=shimpo/><ref>高橋恵子『沖縄の御願ことば辞典』ボーダーインク, p.70</ref> The regions where Kamiashagi are found are classified as the "Kami-asagi Cultural Sphere" and the "Kitayama Cultural Sphere," and are said to overlap with the territory of the [[:en:Hokuzan|Kitayama Kingdom]] prior to the unification of the Three Mountains.<ref>高橋哲朗「沖縄の伝統行事 芸能を歩く」沖縄探見社, p. 59</ref>
== Cultural Properties == The following Kamiashagi have been designated as {{ill|Tangible Folk Cultural Properties|ja|有形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tangible Folk Cultural Properties|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 民俗文化財|1=Folk Cultural Property of Japan|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q24895900}} of Okinawa Prefecture: * [[:en:Iheya, Okinawa|Iheiya Village]] – the Kamiashagi of Gakiya, 1 structure – designated on July 11, 1977 (Showa 52)<ref name=list>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.pref.okinawa.jp/edu/bunkazai/edu/jimukyoku/bunkazai/documents/h25_012.pdf |title=沖縄県教育庁文化財課要覧（平成28th year 度版） 国・県・市町村指定文化財|format=PDF|accessdate=2018-02-08}}</ref> * [[:en:Iheya, Okinawa|Iheiya Village]] – the Kamiashagi of Shima-jiri, 1 structure – designated as above<ref name=list/> * [[:en:Izena, Okinawa|Izena Village]] – the Kamiasagi Worship Hall at Shomimi, 1 structure – designated on February 4, 1994 (Heisei 6)<ref name=list/> * [[:en:Izena, Okinawa|Izena Village]] – the Kamiasagi annex residential site at Nakada, 1 structure – designated as above<ref name=list/> * [[:en:Izena, Okinawa|Izena Village]] – the Kamiasagi Worship Hall at Izena, 1 structure – designated as above<ref name=list/> * [[:en:Izena, Okinawa|Izena Village]] – the Kamiasagi annex residential site at Serikyaku, 1 structure – designated as above<ref name=list/>
